            <title>[GROOVY-2084] Joint groovy/java compiler doesn&apos;t set classpath correctly when path contains spaces in Windows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2084</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you have a path in your classpath that you provide to &amp;lt;groovyc&amp;gt; that contains spaces such as &quot;C:\Documents And Settings\Blah&quot; this causes the classpath to break and compilation errors occur ( on Windows only )&lt;/p&gt;</description>
